              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "sanitize-html legacy XSS advisories are mitigated in current feedback path but version remains risky"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "sanitize-html 1.4.2 is vulnerable per SCA and is used on user-controlled feedback/user fields. The application recursively re-sanitizes in non-challenge mode, which may reduce simple bypasses, but the dependency is old and source review did not conclusively prove all rendered contexts are safe. This is not marked false positive because production XSS risk remains plausible."
              },
              "help": {
